      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09D\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy the decision table into table `J09D_temp` for all records where the tour starts with `J09D`.\\n\\n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09D_temp`.\\n\\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `ENTSCHEIDUNG` using these rules:\\n   - If a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA`.\\n   - Else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`.\\n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` to `EVU`.\\n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` from `500` to `599` to `EVU`.\\n\\n4. Join the table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\\n\\n5. Join the table with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\\n\\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\\n\\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\\n   1. Use the sales customer data table entries.\\n   Else:\\n   1. Use the net customer data table entries.\\n\\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09D`.\\n   Use exactly these column names in the export:\\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`\\n   - `HAUS`\\n   - `ANLAGE`\\n   - `ME_MA_ID`\\n   - `EQUNR`\\n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`\\n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\\n   - `TITLE`\\n   - `FORENAME`\\n   - `SURNAME`\\n   - `STREET`\\n   - `STREETNO`\\n   - `POST_CODE1`\\n   - `CITY1`\\n   - `CITY2`\\n   - `EMAIL`\\n\\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the CSV file attached.\\n   Use file path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\\n\\n10. Delete the temporary table.\\n\\n11. End the process.\"}",
            "id": "lc_285bb1fb-245c-4a41-b5e6-2025e8fc8689"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "614f7024-5949-43ef-a233-6bf0c87f285e",
        "tool_call_id": "call_rpBDxBn7WxctVXiDaz1VdL50",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09D",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy the decision table into table `J09D_temp` for all records where the tour starts with `J09D`.\n\n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09D_temp`.\n\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `ENTSCHEIDUNG` using these rules:\n   - If a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA`.\n   - Else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`.\n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` to `EVU`.\n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` from `500` to `599` to `EVU`.\n\n4. Join the table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\n\n5. Join the table with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\n\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\n\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\n   1. Use the sales customer data table entries.\n   Else:\n   1. Use the net customer data table entries.\n\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09D`.\n   Use exactly these column names in the export:\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`\n   - `HAUS`\n   - `ANLAGE`\n   - `ME_MA_ID`\n   - `EQUNR`\n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`\n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\n   - `TITLE`\n   - `FORENAME`\n   - `SURNAME`\n   - `STREET`\n   - `STREETNO`\n   - `POST_CODE1`\n   - `CITY1`\n   - `CITY2`\n   - `EMAIL`\n\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the CSV file attached.\n   Use file path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\n\n10. Delete the temporary table.\n\n11. End the process."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
